16/11/2021, 3:29 pm - Sukriti Guin: #include<stdio.h>
#include<stdlib.h>
#include<stdbool.h>

void input(int row, int col, int matrix[][col]){
	for(int i=0; i<row; i++){
		for(int j=0; j<col; j++){
			scanf("%d",&matrix[i][j]);
		}
	}
}
void display(int row, int col, int matrix[][col]){
	for(int i=0; i<row; i++){
		for(int j=0; j<col; j++){
			printf("%d ",matrix[i][j]);
		}
		printf("\n");
	}
	printf("\n");
}

bool isParseMatrix(int row, int col, int matrix[][col]){
    int size = 0;
    for(int i=0; i<row; i++){
        for(int j=0; j<col; j++){
            if(matrix[i][j]==0)
                size++;
        }
    }
    if(size>(row*col)/2)
        return true;
    else
        return false;
}
void addMatrix(int row, int col,int matrix1[][col],int matrix2[][col],int summatrix[][col]){
    for(int i=0; i<row; i++){
        for(int j=0; j<col; j++){
            summatrix[i][j] = matrix1[i][j]+matrix2[i][j];
        }
    }
}

int main(){
    int row1, row2, col1, col2;
	printf("Enter the number of rows of 1st matrix : ");scanf("%d",&row1);
	printf("Enter the number of columns of 1st matrix : ");scanf("%d",&col1);
	printf("Enter the number of rows of 2nd matrix : ");scanf("%d",&row2);
	printf("Enter the number of columns of 2nd matrix : ");scanf("%d",&col2);
	int matrix1[row1][col1],matrix2[row2][col2];
	printf("Enter the matrix 1 elements : \n");input(row1,col1,matrix1);
	printf("Enter the matrix 2 elements : \n");input(row2,col2,matrix2);
	int summatrix[row1][col1];
	if(!isParseMatrix(row1,col1,matrix1) && !isParseMatrix(row2,col2,matrix2))
		printf("Not parse matrix");
	else{
		if(row1 != row2 || col1 != col2)
			printf("Add of these two parse matrix is not possible\n");
		else{
			summatrix[row1][col1];
			printf("Summation of two parse matrix is : \n");
			addMatrix(row1,col1,matrix1,matrix2,summatrix);
			display(row1,col1,summatrix);
		}
	}
	// printf("Summation matrix is : ");
	// display(row1,col1,summatrix);

	return 0;
}

18/11/2021, 6:36 pm - Gouranga: Hello ECE-ians🤩🤩

🛑 *This is strictly for ECE 2nd Year Students* 

Fire up the cylinders within and gear up to rise above and beyond as we prepare to search for the *NEXT LEADERS* who'll be taking on the mantle of our glorious storied department.🔥🔥

Hence, we the NSEC ECE Department presents

*2nd YEAR LEADER HUNT*✨

An opportunity for all the second years to join hands and continue the legacy by volunteering for Homecoming 2022: The annual alumni meet up of ECE Department, work for the Department and be the next leaders!

🛑 What to expect?

 • Learn about leadership skills and experience working in a team.
• Get to hear from experienced seniors.
• Domain introduction and division for Homecoming '22!

Make sure to join the session if you wish to become the leaders of tomorrow!❤️

Date: 18th November, 2021
Time: 7:00 PM onwards
Venue: Google Meet

08/12/2021, 9:54 pm - Gaurav Kumar: 💥Warm Rotaract Greetings💥

Winter calls for some fun events and enjoyment which ypu await for the entire year along! 🔥

Hence, *Rotaract Club of Netaji Subhash Engineering College* brings to you *The Rota Carnival 3.0* ✨✨

The Carnival will be having various fun-filled events for all to participate in. From creative events to debates and quizzes, we have it all ready for you 🔥

🎉The event is open for all Rotaractors and Non-Rotaractors🎉

⚫Registration fees(each event) 📒: 
Rotaractors : 10/-
Non-Rotaractors : 15/-

 ⚫Payment details💰:
*Arunima -7478327805 (gpay/phonepe)*
*Subhransu - 8167058426 (gpay/paytm)*

*⚫Registration link®️*: https://forms.gle/2eVgXtvcrugTzwhg6

*⚫CLUB COLLABORATION* :
*Co-hosting* - 3 participants 
*Hosting* - 5 participants
(Mail us the participant list with club logo at rotaractclubnsec@gmail.com) 

⚫Prize:

Appreciation Certificate 📜and medal🎖️to the winners along with promoting them in our social media handles.

Participation Certificate 📜to all the participants. 

⚫*Please follow the below steps to register :*

1. Fill in the Google form with the details of your participation VERY carefully.

2. First, you will need to pay for the events that you are participating in and then take a screenshot of your payment. 

3. Attach the screenshot of your payment in the Google form. Please note, this is absolutely necessary. Otherwise your response won't be accepted. 

4. You can pay for multiple events at one go itself. No need to fill in the form separately for individual events.

5. Join the respective event's group via the invitation link just after you submit your response. Don't join the other groups in which you are not participating unneccesarily.

6. For Mr./Ms. Rotaract you need to send your proper selfie *WITHOUT ANY EDITS / FILTER* at our offcial mail "rotaractclubnsec@gmail.com". After that we will upload that in our fb page and based on the no.of likes , comments, & share it will be judged.

🛑 Categories:

*Offline Events:*
*• Debate  • Quiz  • Jam  • Pic To Press*

*Online Events:*
*• Dance  • Poster making  • Photography  • Fashion Show  • Video editing  • Singing  • Creative Writing  • Mr./Ms. Rotaract*

• Seema Sharma(Vice-President) - 8621882912

16/01/2022, 7:55 pm - Sukriti Guin: HackWithInfy is a coding competition for engineering students graduating in the years 2023, 2024, and 2025 across India. The program is specially designed to inculcate a culture of rapid problem-solving and innovative thinking early in academic life.

HackWithInfy provides the perfect stepping-stone for students to explore their interest in programming and an opportunity to compete and win exciting prizes. The top performers will also earn a chance to work with Infosys.

HackWithInfy comprises two rounds with Round 1 as an individual online test and a Grand Finale. This year, HackWithInfy is not just open to the final year engineering students but also for the second and third-year engineering students in India to prove their mettle and win exciting cash prizes worth INR3.5 Lakhs. Registration to HackWithInfy is open through InfyTQ, the Infosys learning and engagement platform for engineering students in India. If you are an InfyTQ user, click on the HackWithInfy banner on the InfyTQ website homepage to register for the competition. If you are not an InfyTQ user, visit the InfyTQ website to create an account and register for HackWithInfy. For more details, read the terms and conditions of HackWithInfy here.                                                https://www.infosys.com/careers/hackwithinfy.html

7. DECODER 
8. 2D parity checj

10. 0.3
11. -27
12. Ā...

14.A=0,B=1,C=0,D=0

15. Excess 3
16. Sum of min terms
17. (36.206)8
18. 4
19. Sum=0, Cout=1
20. 010011
21. All FF's are preset with data
22. Universal
23. Jk
24. 2khz

26. Propagation

29. Each flip-flop
30. 11111100

36. ECL

Year: 2nd
Semester: 3rd

23/03/2022, 3:18 pm - Sudipta Patra: clc
fc=6000;
Tc=1/fc;
Lc=100*Tc
Ec=2;
tc=0:.001*Lc:Lc;
c=cos(2*pi*fc*tc);
%plot(tc,c)
%normalized message signal
fm=2000;
Tm=1/fm;
Lm=10*Tm;
ts=.001*Lm;
fs=1/ts;
tm=0:ts:Lm;
M_t=cos(2*pi*fm*tm);
%plot(tm,M_t)
m(1)=0 
a=[]
for i=1:1:10
    x=m(i);
    e=Ec+x.*M_t;
    AM=e.*c
    a=[a;AM]
    m(i+1)=m(i)+0.1
end
s1=a(1,:)
s2=a(5,:)
s3=a(10,:)
subplot(3,1,1)
plot(tm,s1)
subplot(3,1,2)
plot(tm,s2)
subplot(3,1,3)
plot(tm,s3)

03/04/2022, 7:26 pm - Rupam: *"এসো হে বৈশাখ, এসো, এসো"* 🌤️

Rotaract Club Of Calcutta Diamond  presents our flagship event *"বৈশাখী"* ❤️💥

*_|| ছোটদের মুখে হাসি ফোটাতে , ছুটে আসছে বৈশাখী... ||_* 😀🎐

*_"বৈশাখী"_* is our _Bengali's New Year Special Event_ where we are going to visit an orphanage. 🏡

*Perks* of the event:

1) We are going to distribute *new clothes* to the orphan kids. 👚👕👖👗
2) We will donate all the *groceries and the necessary ingredients required in cooking to them, which will be cooked and eaten that day.* 🍖🍲 In the meantime we will also spend some of our quality time with the orphan kids. 🧒🏻👦🏻

So let's join together and make this event a *grand* one! 💯🏻

*Date:* 17/04/2021 🌚
*Venue:* Sampark, Haridevpur 41 Pally ✨

Rotaract Club Of Calcutta Diamond  presents our flagship event *"বৈশাখী"* ❤️💥

*_|| ছোটদের মুখে হাসি ফোটাতে , ছুটে আসছে বৈশাখী... ||_* 😀🎐

*_"বৈশাখী"_* is our _Bengali's New Year Special Event_ where we are going to visit an orphanage. 🏡

*Perks* of the event:

1) We are going to distribute *new clothes* to the orphan kids. 👚👕👖👗
2) We will donate all the *groceries and the necessary ingredients required in cooking to them, which will be cooked and eaten that day.* 🍖🍲 In the meantime we will also spend some of our quality time with the orphan kids. 🧒🏻👦🏻

So let's join together and make this event a *grand* one! 💯🏻

*Date:* 17/04/2021 🌚
*Venue:* Sampark, Haridevpur 41 Pally ✨

18/05/2022, 6:20 pm - Gouranga: My Dear Students
*Coursera has stopped offering free courses from 29/03/2022.* 
Now, you enroll (directly) a course from Coursera / Udemy without invitation email and apply for FREE through Financial Aid link

*Steps for https://www.coursera.org :*
Visit (i) coursera.org, (ii) search your desired course (iii) go to course page (iv) if you find a sentence "Financial aid available" then you may get this course as free of cost (v) enroll that course using a new email address / account (vi) again apply for "Financial Aid" after login and enrolment.
You may visit a 3rd party website to know the technique to get a free course from Coursera - https://skillscouter.com/free-coursera-courses/

*Steps for Udemy.com:*
Now most of the short duration courses are available free of cost from Udemy.com
Visit https://www.udemy.com/courses/free/ and search your desired course and enroll that course with a new email address.
You may visit a 3rd party website which suggest how to get a course as a free of cost from Udemy - https://udemyfreecourses.org/
*Remember, a eight (8) hours duration course will give you one (1) credit point*

Thank you and best wishes for learning MOOCs for your Honours Degree

For any doubts you may WhatsApp (preferable) or call me
Regards
PSP Sir

20/05/2022, 12:38 pm - Nishant Sourav: format short;
clear all;
clc;
info=[2 3 1;1 2 3;3 1 2];
b=[9;6;8];
a=[info b];
for i=1:size(a,1)
    for j=i+1:size(a,1)
        key1=a(j,i)./a(i,i);
        a(j,:)=a(j,:)-key1.*a(i,:);
    end
end
x=zeros(1,size(info,2));   %creating a 1 row 4 column matrix having 00
for i=size(a,1):-1:1
    out=sum(a(i,i+1:end-1).*x(i+1:end));
    x(i)=(a(i,end)-out)./a(i,i);
end
fprintf('ansr is %f',x);
20/05/2022, 12:46 pm - Nishant Sourav: clc;
clear all;
close all;
x=[-4 -3 -2 1 0 1 2]
y=[0 4 5 3 10 11 2]
l=length(x);
n=6;
h=((x(l)-x(1))/n);   
s=0.5*(y(1)+y(l)); 8
for i=2:l-1
    s=s+y(i); 8+4=12 ,12 +5 =17
end
s=s.*h;
fprintf('thre required value is %4f \n',s);

15/06/2022, 11:58 pm - Ankit Sammadar: am = input('am =');
fm = input('fm =');
ac= input('ac=');
fc= input('fc=');
m = am/ac;
t= 0 :pi/1000:2*pi; 


subplot (3,1,1)
plot(t,am.*cos(fm*t));
grid on


subplot(3,1,2)
xlabel("time")
plot(t, ac.*cos(fc*t));
title("c(t)")
grid on


subplot(3,1,3) 
xlabel("time")
x= ac*(1+m.*cos(fm*t)).*cos(fc*t);
plot(t, x);
title("AM SGNAL")
grid on

L=length(x)
Fs=10*fc;
NFFT = 2^nextpow2(L)
pxx = fft(x,NFFT);
f = Fs/2*linspace(0,1,NFFT/2+1)
spec=2*abs(pxx(1:NFFT/8+1));
figure()
plot(f(1:NFFT/8+1),pow2db(spec));
%power calculation

fprintf("m= %d\n", m);
ma=m*m;
fprintf("m^2= %d\n",m*m);
sbp= (ac*ac*ma)/8;
dsb= sbp*2;
fprintf("sideband power of a single band = %d Wattand that of double side band is %d \n", sbp, dsb)
pc= (ac*ac)/2;
fprintf("cariier power =%d watt \n", pc);
am_power= pc*(1+ma/2);
fprintf("am_power= %d watt", am_power);
p_carrier=max(abs(pc))
p_carrier_dB=pow2db(pc)
p_sideband=max(abs(sbp))
p_sideband_dB=pow2db(sbp)
15/06/2022, 11:58 pm - Ankit Sammadar: clc
fc=6000;
Tc=1/fc;
Lc=100*Tc
Ec=2;
tc=0:.001*Lc:Lc;
c=cos(2*pi*fc*tc);
%plot(tc,c)
%normalized message signal
fm=2000;
Tm=1/fm;
Lm=10*Tm;
ts=.001*Lm;
fs=1/ts;
tm=0:ts:Lm;
M_t=cos(2*pi*fm*tm);
%plot(tm,M_t)
m(1)=0 
a=[]
for i=1:1:10
    x=m(i);
    e=Ec+x.*M_t;
    AM=e.*c
    a=[a;AM]
    m(i+1)=m(i)+0.1
end
s1=a(1,:)
s2=a(5,:)
s3=a(10,:)
subplot(3,1,1)
plot(tm,s1)
subplot(3,1,2)
plot(tm,s2)
subplot(3,1,3)
plot(tm,s3)

16/06/2022, 12:49 pm - Aritra Bera: am = input('am =');
fm = input('fm =');
ac= input('ac=');
fc= input('fc=');
m = am/ac;
t= 0 :pi/1000:2*pi; 


subplot (3,1,1)
plot(t,am.*cos(fm*t));
grid on


subplot(3,1,2)
xlabel("time")
plot(t, ac.*cos(fc*t));
title("c(t)")
grid on


subplot(3,1,3) 
xlabel("time")
x= ac*(1+m.*cos(fm*t)).*cos(fc*t);
plot(t, x);
title("AM SGNAL")
grid on

L=length(x)
Fs=10*fc;
NFFT = 2^nextpow2(L)
pxx = fft(x,NFFT);
f = Fs/2*linspace(0,1,NFFT/2+1)
spec=2*abs(pxx(1:NFFT/8+1));
figure()
plot(f(1:NFFT/8+1),pow2db(spec));
%power calculation

fprintf("m= %d\n", m);
ma=m*m;
fprintf("m^2= %d\n",m*m);
sbp= (ac*ac*ma)/8;
dsb= sbp*2;
fprintf("sideband power of a single band = %d Wattand that of double side band is %d \n", sbp, dsb)
pc= (ac*ac)/2;
fprintf("cariier power =%d watt \n", pc);
am_power= pc*(1+ma/2);
fprintf("am_power= %d watt", am_power);
p_carrier=max(abs(pc))
p_carrier_dB=pow2db(pc)
p_sideband=max(abs(sbp))
p_sideband_dB=pow2db(sbp)
16/06/2022, 12:49 pm - Aritra Bera: clc
fc=6000;
Tc=1/fc;
Lc=100*Tc
Ec=2;
tc=0:.001*Lc:Lc;
c=cos(2*pi*fc*tc);
%plot(tc,c)
%normalized message signal
fm=2000;
Tm=1/fm;
Lm=10*Tm;
ts=.001*Lm;
fs=1/ts;
tm=0:ts:Lm;
M_t=cos(2*pi*fm*tm);
%plot(tm,M_t)
m(1)=0 
a=[]
for i=1:1:10
    x=m(i);
    e=Ec+x.*M_t;
    AM=e.*c
    a=[a;AM]
    m(i+1)=m(i)+0.1
end
s1=a(1,:)
s2=a(5,:)
s3=a(10,:)
subplot(3,1,1)
plot(tm,s1)
subplot(3,1,2)
plot(tm,s2)
subplot(3,1,3)
plot(tm,s3)
16/06/2022, 12:49 pm - Aritra Bera: clc
clear all;
close all;

fc = 5000;
Tc = 1/fc;    %Time period = 0.00016
Lc = 100 * Tc;    %0.016
tc = 0:0.001*Lc:Lc;
c = cos(2*pi*fc*tc);
%plot(tc,c);

fm = 2000;
Tm = 1/fm;    %0.0005
Lm = 10 * Tm;
%ts = 0.001*Lm;
%fs = 1/ts;
tm = 0:0.001*Lm:Lm;
M_t = cos(2*pi*fm*tm);
%plot(tm,M_t)

Ec = 2;
m(1) = 0
a = []
for i=1:1:10
    x = m(i);   %x = 0 0.1
    e = Ec+x.*M_t;    %e = 1+x.[M_t] e=[1 1 1 1.....1]
    AM = e.*c;    % Am = [1 0.8 ......]
    a = [a;AM];   % a = [ ; 1 0.8.....]   (Ec + x.M_t) * c
    m(i+1) = m(i) + 0.1;
end

s1 = a(1,:);
s2 = a(5,:);
s3 = a(10,:);
subplot(3,1,1)
plot(tm,s1)
subplot(3,1,2)
plot(tm,M_t)
subplot(3,1,3)
plot(tm,s3)

23/06/2022, 3:03 pm - Ankit Sammadar: Analog Circuits
*Jai Shree Ram*

1•Generator output level is held constant
2•Semiconductor
3•increases the input impedance and bandwidth
4•None of the mentioned
5•Smaller than the input voltage
6•Bias transistor
7•Negative halfwave rectifier with two diodes
8•Output voltage = Reference voltage
9• IG=0
    10•2 mA
11•Both 1 and 2
12•1.11
13•Half-wave
14•b)Single
15•Ripple factor
16•Drift of charges
17•Peak factor
18•Vin = Vref
19•LC filter
20•DC inserter
21•a)Source resistance
22•b)NMOS
23•101
24•26
25.Crest
26•812
27•d)both (a) and (c)
28•2.5V
29•Ci=0.1µF and Rd=10kΩ
30•0
31•unfaithful amplification
32•Shift in Q-point
33•Voltage
34•Class C
35•To prevent an increase in the input resistance due to the biasing network
36•225°
37•half power
38•Transistor
39•Because DC currents from both transistors flow in opposite directions
40•70.72 V
41•Size of the transformer required reduces

45•Inductive voltage divider

23•CX

23/08/2022, 4:36 pm - Tathagata: Ans. Of Cyber law
23/08/2022, 4:36 pm - Tathagata: How Digital Signature is used for Authentication of Electronic Document? Digital Signature: Digital Signature is a number which is created using private key of a key pair (combination of private and public key). A user who wants to send a legal valid electronic document should have a key pair. The public key is used for verification and it distributed to agencies like Income Tax Dept, Registrar of Companies etc while private key is for the user himself for creating digital signature.

For any legal valid electronic document, two requirements are there: • Integrity of document i.e. document has not changed once created

⚫ Authentication i.e. document is signed by authorized user.

These requirements are satisfied with the following techniques:

⚫ Hash Function or known as Hashing is used for integrity of document

⚫ Digital Signature used for Authentication of documents.

The following steps are part of creating a legal valid electronic document/message:

(1) Sender creates the electronic document/message (2) Sender executes Hash Function on electronic document and this provides a message digest (i.e. it provides a big number which will change if document's content changes)

(3) This message digest or number is encrypted by using private key and this encrypted number is

known as Digital Signature

(4) Sender sends the electronic document and Digital Signature to receiver (5) Receiver uses the Sender's certified public key and decrypts the Digital Signature and generates the message digest or a number

(6) Receiver executes the Hash Function on received electronic documents and generates a message digest.

09/09/2022, 6:40 pm - Gouranga: Dear Students,
Please ignore my previous mail dated 08.09.22 regarding UT1.  The amended procedure for conduction of UT1 will be as follows:
The students have to complete the examination within the scheduled time (1hr) as indicated in the revised routine (copy attached) and handover the answer scripts to the invigilators as per the normal practice. Respective faculty members/subject teachers will check the answer scripts and will return to the respective students who will be asked to scan their checked answer scripts to submit the pdf. In this regard necessary instructions will be issued by the respective subject teacher.
Finally I would like to make it clear that if any student fails to appear in this offline UT then he/she will not be evaluated for CA3. In this case no online examination can be conducted as an alternative measure.
So I would advise you to act accordingly for attending this offline examination on the scheduled dates.
Best Wishes
HOD-EE

🤩 Warm Rota greetings from Rotaract Club of Calcutta Diamond, R.I.D 3291. 🤩 

We the members of *Rotaract Club Of Calcutta Diamond* are coming up with our biggest flagship event *"ইচ্ছেডানা"* this Durga Puja!! ❤️

This year we're planning to lighten up the lives of the orphan kids in our society. 👦🏻👩🏻

The event will consist of 2 phases: 

➡️ _*PHASE 1:*_
_On a specific puja day we will gift the children of Hope Foundation with new clothes to wear for the festival._  👕👖👚👗

➡️ _*PHASE 2:*_
 _On the day of "Tritiya", 28/09/22, we will organise a pandal hopping for them within Kolkata. They will enjoy the day with us._  🚌🚎

⭐ *Collaboration Criterias* ⭐

🪙 Rotary Club Host - *Rs.500/-*
🪙 Rotary Club Co-Host - *Rs.350/-*
🪙 Rotaract Club Host - *Rs.200/-*
🪙 Rotaract Club Co-Host - *Rs.150/-*

26/09/2022, 6:11 pm - Arnab Basak: Worried about your health while sitting in front of a screen all day long 😟?
Being Physically active and fit holds utmost importance especially among today’s younger generation who is busy enjoying the luxuries of mobile, laptop and TV at an alarming rate and aren’t active and spirited on a daily basis. 😥

Being fit increases energy level and confidence and reduces stress.Basically being physically fit overhauls your whole personality🤩🤩

The official tech club of nsec, Phoenix is organizing a webinar on :- "Fitness and Nutrition-Simplified".
Our very own alumni and founding member of Phoenix, Ritesh Singh (Founder of Hustel &Health ) will be the guest speaker🥳🥳

Topics like how we can stay fit even in low budget, what proper measures to take for staying healthy, etc. will be discussed.
We cordially invite you all to attend this meeting.

 Time: 6 pm onwards

07/01/2023, 10:32 pm - Sudipta Patra: *Greetings from Team Mesmerizer!!* ✨


Mesmerizer is the annual cultural fest of NSEC that aims to celebrate and showcase the diverse cultural talents of students from different colleges. This year, the fest will be held in two phases. 

In the first phase ( *14th and 15th January* ), we will be having the inter college competitions in areas such as music, dance debate, art, and more in the college campus. In the 2nd phase ( *19th January* ), we will have the prize distribution ceremony followed by the guest performance at *Northern Park, Bhawanipur.*📍

Kindly find the attached event brochure, the rulebook and the registration form below.

We have further attached the links for registration for the different events below. 

● *All That Jazz* (Group dance)
https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLScAsNshOS-zCRvGkFQmW9MgFGZs5cIDIs1gCvJKZJ5vtL8Mvw/viewform?usp=sf_link

● *Ghungroo* (Solo dance)
https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSeXdJNPGmy5XWJAf8R_OCkb7vzFOlHDJElHOhaHqQy1cBTxiA/viewform?usp=sf_link

● *Move It* (Street Style)
https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSd7wmZ6jL72ejL7VAg_00vARnK19TZlVUIdnBTPsdu3cy-nBw/viewform?usp=sf_link

● *Talk – Rocks* (Debate)
https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSc1HBYPxhlBHUMm1zQKLZiJWWzuRHY5juO75tAr8NoYeccdYA/viewform?usp=sf_link

● *Mind Fizz* (Quiz)
https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSf2agHcJlCLITUR6tviM8kjNPQYealJJlybWEGb328qJF3qBw/viewform?usp=sf_link

● *Dotaara* (Singing)
https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSeOaax3vk2KiNF8t_5yhOtk7O92ZkxD2C1xolb4BhHj73Q0gQ/viewform?usp=sf_link

● *Glam-Up* (Fashion Show)
https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSfihPGBJspAoBmCNgDSMZdIo_0V7ltsczjcfY1Yj2rM7Ccnsw/viewform?usp=sf_link

● *Paint it up* (Face painting)
https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLScFS5Ap5b7juSGx3HQi2Pfyjyx27uWltwf8a4XVOd8UTRjAsQ/viewform?usp=sf_link

● *Ink and Quill* (Creative writing)
https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSfnVUUo5AKNUT0qQCu8S-C28TUzBLLjIzAbZOpWFzXzbZFZMw/viewform?usp=sf_link
